  1. (6pt) Compute average CO2 emissions per capita across the continents (assume region is the same as continent). Comment what do you see.
co2plot <- cntry[!is.na(cntry$co2_PC) &
                 !is.na(cntry$region) &
                 (cntry$time == 1960 |
                 cntry$time == 2016),] %>% 
  group_by(region,time) %>% 
  summarize(
    avg = sum(co2_PC)/n()
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'region'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

  1. (6pt) Compute the average life expectancy for each continent in 1960 and 2019. Do the results fit with what do you see on the figures?
LE <- cntry[!is.na(cntry$region) & 
            !is.na(cntry$lifeExpectancy) &

  group_by(region, time) %>% 
  summarize(

  1. (6pt) What was the ranking of US in terms of life expectancy in 1960 and in 2019? (When counting from top.)
## 1960
le60 <- cntry[!is.na(cntry$name) &
              !is.na(cntry$lifeExpectancy) &
              (cntry$time == 1960),]

usrank60 <- rank(-(le60$lifeExpectancy), na.last=TRUE, ties.method = "first")[
  which(le60$name == "United States of America")
]

cat("The rank of the US in 1960 was", usrank60)
## The rank of the US in 1960 was 17
## 2019
le19 <- cntry[!is.na(cntry$name) &
              !is.na(cntry$lifeExpectancy) &
              (cntry$time == 2019),]

usrank19 <- rank(-(le19$lifeExpectancy), na.last=TRUE, ties.method = "first")[
  which(le19$name == "United States of America")
]

cat("The rank of the US in 2019 was", usrank19)
## The rank of the US in 2019 was 46
